de.boereck.matcher.helpers

Class ArrayMatchHelpers

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.boereck.matcher.helpers.ArrayMatchHelpers

  • public class ArrayMatchHelpers
extends Object
    Provides static helper functions for defining matches in CaseMatchers based on array values.

    This class is not intended to be instantiated or sub-classed.

      • findCount

        public static <T> Found findCount(T[] arr,
                                  Predicate<? super T> p)
                           throws NullPointerException
        This method traverses the given array arr and checks how many elements in that array are tested positive with the given predicate. Depending on the result, a subclass of Found will be returned. This will either be FoundAll, FoundNone or FoundSome. Be aware that under the covers java stream APIs may be used.
        Type Parameters:
        T - Type of elements of arr.
        Parameters:
        arr - array that will be traversed and elements checked for predicate p.
        p - Predicate, every element from arr is checked with. Must not be null.
        Returns:
        Found instance, based on how many elements in arr pass predicate p.
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - will be thrown if p is null.

        public static <I> TestableToLongFunction<I[]> countInArray(Predicate<? super I> p)
                                                    throws NullPointerException
        Returns a function that counts how many elements of an input array are tested positive with the given predicate p. If the input array is null, the returned count will be 0.
        Type Parameters:
        I - Type of elements in the input collection
        Parameters:
        p - used to check how many elements in the input array match this predicate
        Returns:
        function that counts how many elements of an input collection are tested positive with the given predicate p. If the input collection is null, the returned count will be 0.
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - will be thrown if p is null.

      • containsOrdered

        public static <I> Predicate<I[]> containsOrdered(I key,
                                                 Comparator<? super I> cmp)
                                          throws NullPointerException
        Returns a predicate checking if the given key element exists in an array of elements ordered ascending by the ordering defined in comparator cmp. The predicate will return false if the input array is null.
        Type Parameters:
        I - The type of the input array.
        Parameters:
        key - the element that is searched in input arrays.
        cmp - the comparator defining the order on type I.
        Returns:
        Predicate checking if element key is element in input arrays, ordered by the ordering defined by cmp.
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if cmp is null.
